{"timestamp":1774455929527,"source_app":"agentic-harness","session_id":"52f836f3-345c-41aa-a6b5-dc9aebfb1ee6","hook_event_type":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_012Kq6WfiVeU5WeTs3MshgmG","payload":{"session_id":"52f836f3-345c-41aa-a6b5-dc9aebfb1ee6","transcript_path":"/Users/auto/.claude/projects/-Users-auto-agentic-harness-apps-mas-trees-93056489/52f836f3-345c-41aa-a6b5-dc9aebfb1ee6.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/auto/agentic-harness/apps/mas/trees/93056489","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Write","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/auto/agentic-harness/apps/mas/trees/93056489/specs/issue-93056489-adw-3d4a8a0a-sdlc_planner-add-display-savings-attribute.md","content":"# Plan: Add display-savings attribute to discount template\n\n## Task Description\nAdd a `data-display-savings` attribute to the discount template that renders the absolute dollar savings amount (e.g., \"Save $120/yr\") alongside the existing percentage display (e.g., \"40%\"). When the attribute is absent, behavior must remain identical to the current implementation. Savings are only rendered when positive.\n\n## Relevant Files\n\n- `web-components/src/discount/template.js` \u2014 **Edit**: core change; add savings computation and conditional rendering\n- `web-components/src/discount/index.js` \u2014 Read-only reference; no changes needed\n- `web-components/src/inline-price.js` \u2014 **Edit**: add `data-display-savings` to `observedAttributes` and `createInlinePrice` options\n- `web-components/src/price.js` \u2014 **Edit**: add `displaySavings` to `collectPriceOptions`\n- `web-components/src/price/utilities.js` \u2014 Read-only reference; use existing `formatPrice` for currency formatting\n- `web-components/test/discount/template.test.js` \u2014 **Edit**: add test cases for display-savings behavior\n\n## Step by Step Tasks\n\n### 1. Add `data-display-savings` to `InlinePrice.observedAttributes` in `inline-price.js`\n- In the `observedAttributes` static getter (line ~219), add `'data-display-savings'` to the array\n- In `createInlinePrice`, destructure and forward `displaySavings` in the options passed to `createMasElement`\n\n### 2. Add `displaySavings` to `collectPriceOptions` in `price.js`\n- In `collectPriceOptions` (line ~27), add `displaySavings` to the destructuring of `Object.assign(options, placeholder?.dataset ?? {}, overrides ?? {})`\n- Add `displaySavings: toBoolean(displaySavings)` in the options object returned (follow the same pattern as `displayOldPrice`, `displayPerUnit`, etc.)\n\n### 3. Modify `createDiscountTemplate` in `web-components/src/discount/template.js`\n- Import `formatPrice` from `'../price/utilities.js'`\n- Update `createDiscountTemplate` to receive and use `context` properly (it already receives `context` as first arg of the returned function)\n- After computing `discount`, also compute `savingsAmount = priceWithoutDiscount - price`\n- When `context.displaySavings === true` AND `savingsAmount > 0` AND `discount !== undefined`:\n  - Format the savings using `formatPrice({ formatString: value.formatString, price: savingsAmount, usePrecision: value.usePrecision })` \u2014 use `.accessiblePrice` from the result as the currency-formatted string\n  - Append a `<span class=\"discount-savings\">Save ${formattedSavings}</span>` after the discount percentage span\n- When condition is not met, render only the existing markup (backwards compatible)\n\nExample output when `display-savings` is active:\n```html\n<span class=\"discount\">10%<span class=\"discount-savings\">Save US$3.00</span></span>\n```\nor as a sibling span:\n```html\n<span class=\"discount\">10%</span><span class=\"discount-savings\">Save US$3.00</span>\n```\n\nFollow the existing pattern in the file \u2014 use a sibling span to keep the percentage span intact.\n\n### 4. Add test cases in `web-components/test/discount/template.test.js`\n- Add test: `display-savings` absent \u2192 output is unchanged (existing markup only)\n- Add test: `display-savings` present, savings > 0 \u2192 percentage span + savings span rendered\n- Add test: `display-savings` present, price === priceWithoutDiscount (zero savings) \u2192 no savings span rendered\n- Add test: `display-savings` present, no `formatString` in value \u2192 gracefully omit savings span (defensive)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- When `data-display-savings` attribute is not present, rendered HTML is byte-for-byte identical to current output\n- When `data-display-savings` is present and `priceWithoutDiscount > price > 0`, a savings element appears with the absolute currency amount formatted per the locale `formatString`\n- When savings amount is zero or negative, no savings element is rendered even if `data-display-savings` is set\n- `data-display-savings` appears in `InlinePrice.observedAttributes` so attribute changes trigger re-render\n- `displaySavings` is processed by `collectPriceOptions` with `toBoolean()` consistent with other display flags\n- All existing discount template tests continue to pass\n\n## Validation Commands\n- `node --check web-components/src/discount/template.js`\n- `node --check web-components/src/inline-price.js`\n- `node --check web-components/src/price.js`\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_012Kq6WfiVeU5WeTs3MshgmG"}}
